do this, are you going to do this?

00:38:00.070 --> 00:38:04.930
And I remember looking at the dad
going why are your children calling

00:38:04.930 --> 00:38:06.230
me Asian?

00:38:06.230 --> 00:38:08.890
And he said, "Well, I've
told them now for a month

00:38:08.890 --> 00:38:10.560
that the Cajun lady was coming

00:38:10.560 --> 00:38:13.060
but they don't really
know what Cajun is.

00:38:13.060 --> 00:38:16.940
So, they just assumed
that you're Asian.

00:38:16.940 --> 00:38:19.330
So, we rode back and
we got to their house,

00:38:19.330 --> 00:38:23.800
and like I said they were just
three and five and full of energy.

00:38:23.800 --> 00:38:25.810
And I get out of the
car and I have my guitar

00:38:25.810 --> 00:38:27.110
and I have my gig bag
and I have my suitcase.

00:38:27.110 --> 00:38:30.800
And they are running around and
they're like, "Are you gonna

00:38:30.800 --> 00:38:32.120
to play ball with me, are you
gonna [talking fast sounds]?"

00:38:32.120 --> 00:38:33.420
you know, and all this stuff.

00:38:33.420 --> 00:38:35.170
And I'm there, what?

00:38:35.170 --> 00:38:37.880 position:56%
And the youngest one, when I turned,

00:38:37.880 --> 00:38:39.800
he wanted me to watch
him ride his bike.

00:38:39.800 --> 00:38:43.320
And when I turned he had
taken off all of his clothes.

00:38:43.320 --> 00:38:47.540
And he had put on his dad's roller
blades, which were like this big.

00:38:47.540 --> 00:38:50.730
And he is on his bike and he
is riding all the around yard.

00:38:50.730 --> 00:38:53.340
And he is like look at me,
look at me, look at me!

00:38:53.340 --> 00:38:54.970
And I'm thinking, the
other one has tennis balls

00:38:54.970 --> 00:38:56.270
and he's throwing them at my head.

00:38:56.270 --> 00:38:58.630 position:56%
And I'm there, what am I doing here?

00:38:58.630 --> 00:39:02.090
And all of the sudden, the
little one gets off of his bike,

00:39:02.090 --> 00:39:04.900
kicks off the roller blades and
starts running around the yard.

00:39:04.900 --> 00:39:10.060
And then all of the
sudden he like freezes.

00:39:10.060 --> 00:39:15.250
And I hear this woman yell from
the window, "Oh, my god, Levi,

00:39:15.250 --> 00:39:16.770
do you have to go to the potty?"

00:39:16.770 --> 00:39:19.100
And this is a kid who is frozen.

00:39:19.100 --> 00:39:22.520
He just looks at his
mommy and goes, "Uh-huh."

00:39:22.520 --> 00:39:25.480
So, she comes running
out of the house,

00:39:25.480 --> 00:39:27.180
almost knocks me off the sidewalk.

00:39:27.180 --> 00:39:29.320
And she picks up this kid
and she flings him over

00:39:29.320 --> 00:39:30.620
and he's kicking screaming.

00:39:30.620 --> 00:39:31.920
And he's like, "I'm not going.

00:39:31.920 --> 00:39:33.220
I'm not going.

00:39:33.220 --> 00:39:34.520
I'm not going."

00:39:34.520 --> 00:39:35.820
And she would say,
"But you have to go.

00:39:35.820 --> 00:39:37.120
You have to go."

00:39:37.120 --> 00:39:39.220
And all of the sudden he just,
he stiffens up like this.

00:39:39.220 --> 00:39:46.140
And he screams at the
top of his lungs.

00:39:46.140 --> 00:39:50.700
He goes, "I'm not going
unless that Asian lady comes."

00:39:50.700 --> 00:39:54.650
So, the mom, the mom looks
at me and she goes, ah,

00:39:54.650 --> 00:39:56.130
so I said, all right, you know?

00:39:56.130 --> 00:39:58.510
So, I dropped everything
and we run in the house.

00:39:58.510 --> 00:40:02.300
And we get into, she just opens
the door to this little bathroom.

00:40:02.300 --> 00:40:03.980
I mean, tiny.

00:40:03.980 --> 00:40:06.420
And she puts the little kid
on the little [inaudible]

00:40:06.420 --> 00:40:08.680
on the potty right there.

00:40:08.680 --> 00:40:11.320
And then the five-year-old
comes under the sink and he sits

00:40:11.320 --> 00:40:14.770
under the sink and she just kind
of shoves me in and I'm sort

00:40:14.770 --> 00:40:17.560
of squeezing between
the toilet and the wall.

00:40:17.560 --> 00:40:19.540
And she goes, "Thank you."

00:40:19.540 --> 00:40:21.500
And she closes the door.

00:40:21.500 --> 00:40:24.940
So, I'm sitting in this
bathroom with these kids.

00:40:24.940 --> 00:40:27.160
And they're looking at me
and I'm looking at them.

00:40:27.160 --> 00:40:29.380
And I'm going what in
the heck am I doing?

00:40:29.380 --> 00:40:33.390 position:56%
And so the little one, he is sitting
on the potty and he just does

00:40:33.390 --> 00:40:40.760
like that and he goes, "Asian lady,
tell me a story about Asian land."

00:40:40.760 --> 00:40:44.580
And it was in that moment
that I made up a story

00:40:44.580 --> 00:40:49.450
about the ghost tree based on
a tree we have back at home.

00:40:49.450 --> 00:40:52.860
We have the second largest live
oak in the state of Louisiana

00:40:52.860 --> 00:40:54.860
at my grandmother's house.

00:40:54.860 --> 00:40:59.020
So, I made up this story about this
live oak tree that on October 31st

00:40:59.020 --> 00:41:04.270
if you go into the swamp and you
look at it, it will come to life

00:41:04.270 --> 00:41:07.430
and it will grow eyes and its mouth
will open up and snakes will come

00:41:07.430 --> 00:41:10.130
out and it will turn you into
stone and then it will eat you.

00:41:10.130 --> 00:41:17.790
And so, yeah, I mean, it was a
very successful story I might add.

00:41:17.790 --> 00:41:21.200
And in the process it ended up
begin a very wonderful weekend.

00:41:21.200 --> 00:41:23.950
And I wrote the story
down to send to them

00:41:23.950 --> 00:41:25.420
and one thing led to another.

00:41:25.420 --> 00:41:27.280
Somebody read it.

00:41:27.280 --> 00:41:30.390
Within a week I had an
illustrator, a publisher,

00:41:30.390 --> 00:41:33.210
and a book deal and there it was.

00:41:33.210 --> 00:41:34.510
&gt;&gt; Steve Winick: All right.

00:41:34.510 --> 00:41:36.800
